  description: "uuid.SafeUUID.safe.__class__.__name__.__eq__('SafeUUID')==True / SafeUUID.unsafe.__class__.__name__.__eq__('SafeUUID')==True / SafeUUID.__name__.__eq__('SafeUUID')==True / SafeUUID.__module__.__eq__('uuid')==True — SafeUUID.safe.__class__.__name__ is 'SafeUUID' (8 chars; SafeUUID.safe is an instance of the SafeUUID enum class; SafeUUID.safe.__class__ is SafeUUID itself; for enum members, __class__.__name__ returns the enum class name; SafeUUID.safe has value 0 and indicates a UUID was generated safely; uuid.UUID().__is_safe is SafeUUID.safe (value 0) when the UUID was generated via os.urandom()); SafeUUID.unsafe.__class__.__name__ is 'SafeUUID' (8 chars; SafeUUID.unsafe is also a SafeUUID instance; SafeUUID.unsafe has value -1 and indicates unsafe generation; both .safe and .unsafe are members of the same SafeUUID enum and share __class__.__name__=='SafeUUID'); SafeUUID.__name__ is 'SafeUUID' (confirmed; 8 chars; the class name); SafeUUID.__module__ is 'uuid' (confirmed; 4 chars; first uuidsafe159 anchor for SafeUUID member class names)"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: identity
  id_prefix: uuidsafe159

  columns: [id, function, args, expected, description]
  rows:
    - [safe_member_class,    "SafeUUID.safe.__class__.__name__.__eq__",   ["SafeUUID"], true, "uuid.SafeUUID.safe.__class__.__name__ == 'SafeUUID' (8 chars; .safe is a SafeUUID enum instance; value 0; indicates safe UUID generation via os.urandom())"]
    - [unsafe_member_class,  "SafeUUID.unsafe.__class__.__name__.__eq__", ["SafeUUID"], true, "uuid.SafeUUID.unsafe.__class__.__name__ == 'SafeUUID' (8 chars; .unsafe is a SafeUUID enum instance; value -1; indicates unsafe generation)"]
    - [safe_uuid_name_b,     "SafeUUID.__name__.__eq__",                  ["SafeUUID"], true, "uuid.SafeUUID.__name__ == 'SafeUUID' (confirmed; 8 chars; the class whose instances are .safe and .unsafe)"]
    - [safe_uuid_module_b,   "SafeUUID.__module__.__eq__",                ["uuid"],     true, "uuid.SafeUUID.__module__ == 'uuid' (confirmed; 4 chars; Lib/uuid.py; same module as UUID class and generator functions)"]

