table uuid_extra159.SafeUUID_member_values:
  description: "uuid.SafeUUID.safe.value.__eq__(0)==True / SafeUUID.unsafe.value.__eq__(-1)==True / SafeUUID.safe.__class__.__name__.__eq__('SafeUUID')==True / SafeUUID.__bases__[0].__name__.__eq__('Enum')==True — SafeUUID.safe.value is 0 (SafeUUID.safe is the enum member representing safe UUID generation; its integer value is 0; safe generation uses cryptographically strong random sources such as os.urandom(); uuid4() sets is_safe=SafeUUID.safe (value 0) when the OS provides a safe random source; the .value attribute on a plain Enum member returns the underlying value — here 0); SafeUUID.unsafe.value is -1 (SafeUUID.unsafe is the enum member representing unsafe UUID generation; its integer value is -1; the negative value -1 signals 'not safe'; uuid4() may set is_safe=SafeUUID.unsafe (value -1) when the OS cannot guarantee cryptographic randomness; -1 < 0: unsafe(−1) < safe(0)); SafeUUID.safe.__class__.__name__ is 'SafeUUID' (confirmed; 8 chars; both members are instances of SafeUUID); SafeUUID.__bases__[0].__name__ is 'Enum' (confirmed; 4 chars; plain Enum not IntEnum); first uuidsafe159 anchor for SafeUUID member values"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: identity
  id_prefix: uuidsafe159

  columns: [id, function, args, expected, description]
  rows:
    - [safe_value_0,         "SafeUUID.safe.value.__eq__",   [0],  true, "uuid.SafeUUID.safe.value == 0 (safe UUID generation; value 0; safe uses os.urandom() or equivalent; uuid4() sets is_safe=SafeUUID.safe when OS is reliable)"]
    - [unsafe_value_neg1,    "SafeUUID.unsafe.value.__eq__", [-1], true, "uuid.SafeUUID.unsafe.value == -1 (unsafe UUID generation; value -1; negative sentinel; unsafe(-1) < safe(0); indicates lack of guaranteed randomness)"]
    - [safe_cls_name_b,      "SafeUUID.safe.__class__.__name__.__eq__",   ["SafeUUID"], true, "uuid.SafeUUID.safe.__class__.__name__ == 'SafeUUID' (confirmed; 8 chars; both members are SafeUUID instances)"]
    - [bases_enum_b,         "SafeUUID.__bases__[0].__name__.__eq__",     ["Enum"],     true, "uuid.SafeUUID.__bases__[0].__name__ == 'Enum' (confirmed; 4 chars; plain Enum not IntEnum; mro: SafeUUID->Enum->object)"]

