  description: "uuid.SafeUUID.__name__.__len__()==8 / SafeUUID.__module__.__len__()==4 / SafeUUID.__bases__[0].__name__.__len__()==4 / SafeUUID.safe.value.__eq__(0)==True — SafeUUID.__name__.__len__() is 8 ('SafeUUID' = 'Safe'=4 + 'UUID'=4 = 8 chars; the two halves of the name are equal in length: 4+4=8; 'SafeUUID'(8) == 'uuid4'.__len__()(5) < 'SafeUUID'(8): no, 'uuid4'=5 < 'SafeUUID'=8 by 3; comparing to uuid.UUID.__name__.__len__()==4 (uuid_extra157 anchors): 'UUID'(4) vs 'SafeUUID'(8) = SafeUUID is double the length of UUID by prepending 'Safe'=4); SafeUUID.__module__.__len__() is 4 ('uuid' = 4 chars; same 4-char module as UUID class; SafeUUID.__module__.__len__()==UUID.__module__.__len__()==4; also same length as SafeUUID.__bases__[0].__name__.__len__()==4 ('Enum'=4)); SafeUUID.__bases__[0].__name__.__len__() is 4 ('Enum' = 4 chars; 'Enum'(4) == 'uuid'(4) == 'UUID'(4) — a three-way tie; all 4 chars; 'Enum'(4) < 'SafeUUID'(8) by 4); SafeUUID.safe.value is 0 (confirmed; safe==0; unsafe==-1; the value attribute returns the underlying enum value; first uuidsafe159 anchor for SafeUUID name lengths)"
  kind: python_call_eq
